      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(google): enable vertex image and video generation",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nVertex AI generative video currently experiences SDK integration failures when fetching credentials dynamically during the predictLongRunning and polling lifecycle via `gaxios`. This patch safely unblocks video generation by explicitly identifying `google-vertex` requests and routing them to a robust REST fallback path.\n\n- Registers proper runtime capabilities for the `google-vertex` identifier for both image and video generation providers.\n- Adds proper project and location resolution for Vertex AI based on environment variables or config.\n- Bypasses the `@google/genai` SDK and explicitely routes video `predictLongRunning` correctly through Vertex regional domains instead of AI Studio.\n- Updates polling logic to use the `fetchPredictOperation` POST verb mandated by Vertex AI.\n- Adapts generated video response parsing to handle Vertex-specific `videos: [{bytesBase64Encoded: ...}]` payload structure.\n- Explicitly handles `google-vertex` path building for image generation endpoint (`generateContent`).\n- Preserves the `qa-lab` allowlist check by discarding unrelated test changes.\n\nFixes #90209.\n\n## Verification\n\nUnit tests validation passes successfully:\n```\nnpx vitest run src/media-generation/provider-capabilities.contract.test.ts\n\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  2 passed (2)\n   Start at  00:02:57\n   Duration  567ms (transform 296ms, setup 0ms, import 450ms, tests 3ms, environment 0ms)\n```\n\n**Real behavior proof**: Verified successful image and video generation locally running via CLI `google-vertex` with local authentication configuration. Both artifacts generated and extracted locally.\n\n### Image generation proof:\n```\nnpx tsx src/entry.ts capability image generate --model google-vertex/gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview --prompt \"A cute small tuxedo rutin chicken with cyber goggles on an RGB keyboard\" --output /tmp/test_image.png\n\n...\nimage.generate via local\nprovider: google-vertex\nmodel: gemini-3.1-flash-image-preview\noutputs: 1\n/tmp/test_image.png\n\nfile /tmp/test_image.png\n/tmp/test_image.png: PNG image data, 1408 x 768, 8-bit/color RGB, non-interlaced\n```\n\n### Video generation proof:\n```\nGOOGLE_CLOUD_LOCATION=us-central1 OPENCLAW_DEBUG=1 npx tsx src/entry.ts capability video generate --model google-vertex/veo-3.1-fast-generate-001 --prompt \"A cute small tuxedo rutin chicken with cyber goggles pecking on an RGB keyboard\" --duration 5 --output /tmp/test_video.mp4\n\n...\nThe project/location from the environment variables will take precedence over the API key from the environment variables.\n[DEBUG] requestGoogleVideoJson URL: POST https://us-central1-aiplatform.googleapis.com/v1/projects/nyu-ai-gemini/locations/us-central1/publishers/google/models/veo-3.1-fast-generate-001:predictLongRunning\n[DEBUG] requestGoogleVideoJson URL: POST https://us-central1-aiplatform.googleapis.com/v1/projects/nyu-ai-gemini/locations/us-central1/publishers/google/models/veo-3.1-fast-generate-001:fetchPredictOperation\n[DEBUG] requestGoogleVideoJson URL: POST https://us-central1-aiplatform.googleapis.com/v1/projects/nyu-ai-gemini/locations/us-central1/publishers/google/models/veo-3.1-fast-generate-001:fetchPredictOperation\n[DEBUG] requestGoogleVideoJson URL: POST https://us-central1-aiplatform.googleapis.com/v1/projects/nyu-ai-gemini/locations/us-central1/publishers/google/models/veo-3.1-fast-generate-001:fetchPredictOperation\nvideo.generate via local\nprovider: google-vertex\nmodel: veo-3.1-fast-generate-001\noutputs: 1\n/tmp/test_video.mp4\n\nfile /tmp/test_video.mp4\n/tmp/test_video.mp4: ISO Media, MP4 Base Media v1 [ISO 14496-12:2003]\n```\n\n",
        "branch": "fix-google-vertex-video-gen",
